<br>
&quot;Um, them giants go some back up, lets chopp em down to size &quot;<br>
<br>
As the army approaches, The White Warrior notices this army is a detail from Triton, and braces himself for a very bloody battle.<br>
<br>
The army continues past The White Warrior, then stops, and digs in to fight a different battle, one with the Giants.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, guess we weren't handling these giants good enough, Verant sent us back up!&quot;<br>
<br>
If only that where so, for this invading army ruthlessly slaughters any of the gaints who dare to challange us. Then out of the army approaches, a large STOOOOOPID ogre. Being The White Warrior, I quickly stand in his way, tighten my belt, and cross my arms. He dares to tell me, &quot;Leave triton's premisis now!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;HA! I Listen to no one, I am The White Warrior, back down, and your death will be less painful, This is Exodus Fellowship's Land, so get the h e double hockeysticks off it!&quot;<br>
<br>
the stoopid ogre takes a death breath. &quot;We will not be responsible for any deaths.&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;Good thing you brought clerics then!&quot; i thought to myself, but held my tongue as I saw he was from The Guardain Lords, not Triton. Then, before i could return a response, the ogre challanged me to a duel to the death.<br>
<br>
&quot;OOOOhhh i'm soooo scared, picking on the smallest warrior you can find, REAL big of you, i wish i could be as brave as you are!!! Go talk to Krugan, he's more your size! Hey Krugan are you scared too??&quot;<br>
<br>
Krugan screams in false terror, &quot;AHHHHHHH!!!&quot; Then he challanges the stoopid ogre to a duel tot he death. In response to this overwhelming defense, The stupid ogre ran like the wind back to the army.<br>
<br>
Seeing the enemy in retreat, I gave chase, but soon stopped when i saw a better opertunity. Having Ran into front lines like they where the best, the giants attacked with a full out frontal assault. With everyone busy fighting giants, that the Exodus Fellowship should be dispatching, they had no one to remove the giant's corpses for them, so i took liberty to do so.<br>
Sensing their loot in danger, several Triton members return to the corpse to fight over 1st to loot, but i was to fast, and grabed :<br>
<br>
Gladiator's Chain Leggings <br>
LORE ITEM NO DROP <br>
AC: +17 Str: +2 Wis: +6 Cha: +4 Magic Resist: +10 HP: +20 <br>
Weight: 0.0 <br>
Classes: Ranger Shaman Druid Cleric Paladin Shadowknight Bard Rogue Warrior <br>
Races: All Races <br>
Inventory Slot: Legs <br>
<br>
Level to obtain: 58<br>
<br>
and:<br>
<br>
Idol of Disease, which is 1 of 4 idols needed for a cleric bracer from PoA ( has 10wis and a bunch of other stats)<br>
<br>
As normal with The White Warrior, msn was lagging me out so i hit my lag test button which emotes &quot;Khaba kicks modem&quot;<br>
which soon annoyed a triton member named Zaar, who quickly said &quot;No one cares about your modem man! GO AWAY!!&quot;<br>
<br>
I responded &quot;Ohh, did i annoy the poor lil triton person, does he want me to leave him alone, should i kick him instead of modem, wait, don't want to hurt him&quot;<br>
<br>
Well that quickly embarrased Zaar, he nothing to say back! and all his buddies were laughing at him!! so i placed on my new pants, and an idol i can't use, and walked back to our encampment, and was off to the Nexus to fight another day!<br>
<br>
Special Thanks to Triton, with help from The Guardain Lords, and a couple of other guilds for my new pants!!<br>
